# Raisely Prototype Rules

## Design System
All prototypes must follow the Raisely design kit located in `/raisely-pm-visual-kit/`.
- Use styles from `/raisely-pm-visual-kit/styles/` — do not invent new CSS variables or override existing ones
- Use assets from `/raisely-pm-visual-kit/assets/` for logos, icons, and imagery
- Reference `/raisely-pm-visual-kit/readme.md` and any `.md` files for component and usage guidelines
- Match the HTML patterns shown in `/raisely-pm-visual-kit/*.html` for structure and class naming

## Prototype Standards
- All prototypes are static HTML/CSS (no frameworks unless already in the design kit)
- Mobile-responsive by default
- No placeholder lorem ipsum — use realistic Raisely-style copy (fundraising, campaigns, donations)
- Each prototype lives in its own folder under `/prototypes/`
- Each prototype should be self-contained in a single folder so it can be deployed via Netlify Drop for stakeholder sharing.

## Tone / Context
These are feature mockups and campaign pages for a fundraising platform called Raisely.
Stakeholders reviewing these expect them to look like production Raisely pages.